CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FThe consensus at the top of the Labour
OL,8,FParty appears to be that Keir Starmer
OL,9,Fwon't announce a timetable for his
OL,10,Fdeparture until Andy Burnham fights
OL,11,Fthe Makerfield by-election. But that
OL,12,Fmakes very little sense to me.
OL,14,FBecause the probability that he can
OL,15,Fsurvive as PM, even if Burnham were to
OL,16,Flose the by-election, is low.
OL,18,FThis is what his cabinet colleagues
OL,19,Fand trade union leaders have made
OL,20,Fclear to him (and to me).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
