FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FSo the timing and manner of his exit
OL,8,Fare now at the mercy of events, which
OL,9,Fmakes him a lame duck prime minister -
OL,10,Fwhose utterances about policy will
OL,11,Fbarely be heard above the racket of
OL,12,Fspeculation about how and when he will
OL,13,Fgo.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FThis would be humiliating for any PM,
OL,8,Fbut perhaps doubly so for Starmer,
OL,9,Fgiven that his genuine success in
OL,10,Ftaking Labour to a landslide victory
OL,11,Fafter the nadir of the 2019 election
OL,12,Fwould risk being forgotten and ignored
OL,13,Fif his last weeks in office are
OL,14,Fspectacularly chaotic.
OL,16,FThe limitations on his power are
OL,17,Falready conspicuous.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FAs his closest colleagues tell me, he
OL,8,Fwas only powerful enough to do the
OL,9,Fmost limited and unambitious of
OL,10,Freshuffles to fill the vacancy at
OL,11,Fhealth created by Wes Streeting's
OL,12,Fresignation - although the disaster of
OL,13,Flast week's elections would have been
OL,14,Fthe trigger for a more comprehensive
OL,15,Freshaping of the Cabinet if the PM
OL,16,Fwere stronger.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FStarmer lacks the authority to force
OL,8,Fany of his ministers to move or leave
OL,9,Fthe government. It's telling that the
OL,10,FHome Secretary Shabana Mahmood kept
OL,11,Fher job even after her allies briefed
OL,12,Fshe told the PM his time is up, and
OL,13,Fthat Streeting dictated the timing of
OL,14,Fhis own resignation, even though his
OL,15,Fenforcers were actively briefing
OL,16,Fagainst the PM.
OL,18,FIn the Cabinet, the prime minister is
OL,19,Fsupposed to be the first among equals.
OL,20,FIn Starmer's case, scrap "the first"
OL,21,Fand maybe insert "second".
OL,26,@|D@ZOU|D@dO]}D@ROU}D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
