CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FAlso, resignations and sackings over
OL,8,Fthe past few months have left his
OL,9,FDowning Street team depleted. As even
OL,10,Fhis friends tell me, few want to take
OL,11,Fa career risk by working for him,
OL,12,Fpartly because of the open secret that
OL,13,Fhe won't be in post much longer (and
OL,14,Fpartly because the Whitehall zeitgeist
OL,15,Fis that he is the worst kind of
OL,16,Fdelegator, one who insists on
OL,17,Fdelegating but then shows little
OL,18,Floyalty or understanding when things
OL,19,Fgo wrong).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FSo what's the alternative to him being
OL,8,Fin office but not in power, as it were?
OL,10,FPerhaps he should emulate Tony Blair,
OL,11,Fdespite many in his party having
OL,12,Frepudiated the Blair years. In
OL,13,FSeptember 2006, Blair announced he
OL,14,Fwould resign within a year and he
OL,15,Fstood down the following June.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778875556
OL,3,CPeston: Will Starmer announce a
OL,4,Cdeparture timetable sooner than people
OL,5,Cthink?
OL,7,FThis longer timetable meant Blair
OL,8,Fwasn't tainted by the chaos of
OL,9,Funexpected immediate elections. And
OL,10,Fbecause the election schedule was
OL,11,Fdictated by him rather than by factors
OL,12,Fbeyond his control, he looked
OL,13,Fcommensurately stronger. He appeared
OL,14,Fto be the master of events, not the
OL,15,Fvictim.
OL,17,FThe "will he? won't he?" about Starmer
OL,18,Flast week was exhausting just to
OL,19,Fnarrate, as I had to do. Goodness
OL,20,Fknows how bad it was for the main
OL,21,Fprotagonist, Starmer.
OL,26,@yD@EOUyD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
